Defendant Matthew L Appleton in court with attorney Victor E Plantinga.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Parties are prepared to proceed. State placed negotiations on the record. Letter from Children's Hospital on behalf of the defendant received and filed. Statements made as to sentencing.

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 38 MONTHS, with credit for 8 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 20 MONTHS.  

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 24 MONTHS with the following conditions:
1) Pay restitution in the amount of $208.41 to Jacqueline G. Restitution to be paid FIRST before costs, fees and surcharges. Restitution to be paid joint and several with case 15CF403;
2) Pay all costs, fees, surcharges, and restitution during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
3) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;
4) No contact with the victim or the co-defendant Roman Lovelace;
5) Participate in educational or vocational programming once medically cleared;
6) Participate in a cognitive thinking class;
7) Maintain absolute sobriety;

Defendant to enter into a payment plan with the probation agent;

If revoked, defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

If revoked, court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds/wages.

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
